Distribution.
Saetheria reissi Jackson
is quite widespread in the West Europen (
Saether & Spies 2004
). This species was so far reported from North Korea and Japan (
Sasa & Kondo 1993
;
Ree 2009
;
Saether et al. 2000
). In Russian
S. reissi
is known from Angara River near Irkutsk Townes by original description (
Jackson 1977
). This species is widespread in Russian Far East: Primorye, Khabarovsk and Amur Territories, Magadan and Sakhalin Regions, Sokha Republic (Yakutia) (
Makarchenko et al. 2005
).
